# aloha-kids-game — Cursor Project Rules

## Identity

This is a Tauri-based kids' game platform. The Tauri shell (Rust) hosts multiple TypeScript game SPAs.
Each game is a self-contained single-page application. **Child delight comes first.**

## Always Load at Session Start

1. Read `.agent/DNA/PROJECT_DNA.md` — Quick Check section minimum
2. Read `.agent/rules/README.md` — rule routing table

## Hard Blocks — Never Do Without Human Approval

- Push directly to `main`/`master`
- Use `any` type in game logic
- Use `!` non-null assertion on Tauri IPC responses or user input
- Commit credentials or API keys
- Add shared mutable state across game modules

## TypeScript Rules (BLOCK)

- No `any` types in production code — use `unknown` + type guard
- No bare `catch` blocks that swallow errors
- No fire-and-forget `invoke()` calls — always `await` with error handling
- No `console.log` in production code paths — use structured logger

## TDD Rules (BLOCK)

- Write a failing test BEFORE production code
- Run `npx vitest run 2>&1 | tail -40` before marking any task complete
- Mock all `@tauri-apps/api` imports in unit tests

## Error Handling (BLOCK)

- All fallible operations must return a `Result<T, E>` type or throw with full context
- Errors must include operation name and relevant inputs in the message

## Code Style (WARN)

- `const` over `let`; never `var`
- Max function body: 40 lines
- Functions with > 3 params → use a config interface

## DNA Quick Check

```
Stack:    TypeScript / Tauri / Vite / Vitest
Priority: Child delight > Correctness > Performance > Maintainability
Test cmd: npx vitest run
Type cmd: npx tsc --noEmit
```

